I think my problem is not necessarily a bug, but asking before on [SO](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/50257655/how-to-use-pybind11-with-cmake-for-linking-2-modules), gitter and an [old related issue](https://github.com/pybind/pybind11/issues/387#issuecomment-387895612), didn't lead to solutions which solved the issue. Futhermore i think this issue might come up more frequently and can thus be of use for others.

## Issue description
Am trying to create and bind the following two modules with pybind11:
- point: can be called directly
- line: can be called directly and also uses point module.
Trying to use use the line module leads to an undefined symbol error:
`Symbol not found: __ZN5pointC1Eddd`

